{"id":1937,"date":"2014-05-14T16:50:04","date_gmt":"2014-05-14T11:20:04","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/?p=1937"},"modified":"2023-05-23T19:36:16","modified_gmt":"2023-05-23T14:06:16","slug":"cloud-technology-with-unlimited-data-storage-capability","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/blog\/cloud-technology-with-unlimited-data-storage-capability.html","title":{"rendered":"Cloud Technology with unlimited data storage capability"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Cloud technology is certainly the future of business. Given that there is an ample amount of information right from maintaining customer information to a stack of records that you cannot afford to lose, storing and accessing this huge lump of information becomes a challenge for any enterprise.<\/p>\n<p>Engineers had been working on the concept of digitalizing entire information and putting them together as a common source, something that reduces the cost of expensive hardware. Though there were other solutions, nothing could free you from hardware, data storage limit, and location-bound access. Thanks to the ever-evolving technology that finally came up with a brilliant solution &#8211; Cloud technology. It is basically a distributed network or internet-based technology that devices, virtual servers to store data. It enables to access any amount of information onto one platform from anywhere in the world, and on top of it, from any mobile device. Well, that\u2019s called a smart and out-of-the-box solution.<\/p>\n<p>Enterprises are facing this constant challenge to maintain huge data and access it to make their business process more fluid to streamline work and hence, generate more profits. The advent of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.hiddenbrains.com\/cloud-integration-service.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">cloud integration<\/a> has transformed the way information used to flow. A very fine example of cloud computing is certain online document management systems wherein documents can be stored, edited in real-time, and can be shared and accessed by multiple users.<\/p>\n<p>Cloud computing systems for enterprises have resulted in dynamic information flow systems that have facilitated easy and fast workflow with enhanced performance and efficiency. There is an increasing demand for the technology infrastructure as businesses are facing multiple pressures from different digs. Speedier responses at reduced expenses, and adaptable and agile operations, are some of the expected outcomes from IT infrastructure leading to prompting demands on the network. Software-Defined Networking (SDN) aims to address the rising demands of enterprises and is set to emerge as the nerve-center of organizations of the future.<\/p>\n<p>SDN offers a huge number of benefits both to the networking and cloud community. Owing to its unpredictability, and the presence of legacy systems, the chances of quick Software-Defined Networking adoption by enterprises are less. For an enterprise to leave on this SDN journey on its own without the required expertise would have a huge effect on expense and resources, infrastructure, and staff.&nbsp; Bringing in an expert partner would therefore help evade the basic pitfalls and effect a smooth transition.<\/p>\n<p>The adoption of SDN technology will be steady over many years as with previous critical networking waves, for example, Ethernet connectivity, IP internetworking, VoIP, wireless LANs, etc. The complete market acceptance and widespread deployment will take five-ten years to develop.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Cloud technology is certainly the future of business. Given that there is an ample amount of information right from maintaining customer information to a stack of records that you cannot afford to lose, storing and accessing this huge lump of information becomes a challenge for any enterprise. Engineers had been working on the concept of [&hellip;]<\/p>\n